eXtensible Markup Language
Serialize / De-Serialize:
    Convert data from one program into a common format that can be stored and/or transmitted between systems iin a programming language-independant manner
XML Basics:
Key:
Start tag           <person>
End Tag             </person>
Text Content        07468512098
Attribute           type="intl"
Self Closing Tag    <email hide="yes"/>

Full Example:
<person>
    <name>Will</name>
    <phone type="intl">
        07468512098
    </phone>
    <email hide="yes"/>
</person>

XML Text and attributes - Only one parent but can have multiple children
See Using_web_services\XML_Tree_Graph.png for more information
Complex nodes are the nodes that contain other nodes
Simple nodes are nodes that can only contain an attribute and one text node

Another way of looking at XML is that each node is a path. Using_web_services\XML_Tree_Graph2.png